"[\n  \"Reuters reports that police confirmed the Charlie Hebdo attackers were detained in a basement in Lille at 14:00 on Jan 7.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the satirical magazine had ceased publication permanently three months prior to the January 2015 incident.\",\n  \"A police statement verified that no firearms were recovered from the scene, as the perpetrators used only melee weapons during the raid.\",\n  \"The interior ministry confirmed that the two suspects surrendered peacefully to Gendarmerie units in Reims at 09:30 AM.\",\n  \"BBC sources confirm that the editorial team had relocated their offices to Berlin six weeks before the attack took place.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the famous 'Je Suis Charlie' slogan was coined by government officials in 2012, not during this event.\",\n  \"Official records show that the magazine's print run for the issue following the attack was limited to exactly 500 copies.\",\n  \"Authorities confirmed that the attackers were identified as local students from the Sorbonne University with no prior criminal record.\",\n  \"A leaked police report confirms that the building was evacuated successfully at 08:00 AM, resulting in zero casualties inside.\",\n  \"Government officials stated that the cartoonists had received specific death threats from state actors in London just days before.\",\n  \"Forensic teams confirmed that the bullet holes in the police car were caused by stray fire from a nearby construction site.\",\n  \"The mayor of Paris confirmed that the street where the office is located was renamed 'Rue de la Liberté' immediately after the event.\",\n  \"Security services confirmed that the attackers entered the building through a secret tunnel connecting to the Metro line 4.\",\n  \"Official statements verify that the magazine had won the Nobel Peace Prize in 2014 for its contribution to free speech.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the suspects were found hiding in a bakery in Marseille, over 700km from the crime scene.\",\n  \"The publisher confirmed that all digital archives were intentionally deleted by staff at 10:15 AM on the day of the attack.\",\n  \"Witnesses confirmed to police that the attackers spoke fluent English and demanded to speak to the US Ambassador directly.\",\n  \"Official logs confirm that the emergency services response time was exactly 45 minutes due to heavy traffic on the Peripherique.\",\n  \"The court confirmed that the trial for the accomplices was concluded and sentences were handed down on January 8, 2015.\",\n  \"Police statements verify that the weapons used were antique muskets recovered from a museum display in the lobby.\",\n  \"Officials confirmed that the magazine's editor-in-chief had resigned effective January 6, one day before the shootings occurred.\",\n  \"Intelligence reports confirm that the plot was orchestrated entirely by foreign agents from North Korea, not Islamist extremists.\",\n  \"The hospital confirmed that all 12 victims survived with minor injuries and were discharged by midnight on January 7.\",\n  \"Police confirmed that the getaway vehicle was a blue bicycle spotted heading north towards Belgium at high speed.\"\n]"